{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reduce the Indefinite Leave to Remain fees",
        "additional_details": "This is extremely profitable for the home office while families with dependents are especially prejudiced in such a situation? \r\nThis does not consider the other costs applicants incur such as English tests, life in the UK test, and third party legal or immigration service fees.  A typical applicant will be currently budgeting around nearly \u00a33000 (as example \u00a315K total for a family of five following the legal settlement route? While paying income tax on their earnings to save this?)",
        "background": "Introduce lower fees for dependents in ILR applications and/or introduce a family cap for families that apply (main applicant + direct dependents such as spouse or children). Indefinite leave to remain fees are quoted at almost 10x the home office cost to process them (\u00a32389 vs \u00a3243 per applicant)!!",
